<p align="left">
In the payment overview, all payments are displayed with accompanying information.<br />
<br />
By default, NOT Cancelled entries are displayed. To view other entries, then<br />
please click on the arrow symbols (up = NOT Cancelled, Down = Cancelled, right = Show all).<br />
You can also change the sorted order. Standard Sort by Date (newest entries first).<br />
<br />
If you want to add the new payment, then click on New. The selection list shows<br />
only customers whose accounts have not been fully paid. After selecting a customer<br />
the associated data is displayed such as customer number, invoice number, payment method etc.<br />
<br />
If you change data such as the date, then it is necessary either the TAB key to<br />
press or to click another field for the changes to be adopted.<br />
After you click Save, the payment is saved. (Table: payment)<br />
If payment method was cash/bar (No. 2) then additional entry will be saved to cashbook table.<br />
<br />
Note:<br />
<br />
Payments can not be deleted. Payment can be cancelled from the info page.<br />
(Administrator and User Group Manager and Root)<br />
